            <title>[LU-12589] sanity test_102a: setfattr: /mnt/lustre/f102a.sanity: Numerical result out of range</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12589</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity test 102a failed on ppc64 client as follows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 102a: user xattr test ================================================================= 20:53:16 (1563828796)
set/get xattr...
trusted.name1=&quot;value1&quot;
user.author1=&quot;author1&quot;
listxattr...
remove xattr...
set lustre special xattr ...
lfs setstripe: setstripe error for &apos;/mnt/lustre/f102a.sanity&apos;: stripe already set
getfattr: Removing leading &apos;/&apos; from absolute path names
setfattr: /mnt/lustre/f102a.sanity: Numerical result out of range
 sanity test_102a: @@@@@@ FAIL: /mnt/lustre/f102a.sanity doesn&apos;t ignore setting trusted.lov again
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

